#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.46:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:0.2"
msgid "5. Uposathavagga "
msgstr "5. Sabbath "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 46. Anuruddhasutta → anuruddhamanāpakāyikasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.46:0.3"
msgid "46. Anuruddhasutta "
msgstr "46. Anuruddha and the Agreeable Deities "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.263, sc1
msgctxt "an8.46:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anuruddho divāvihāraṃ gato hoti paṭisallīno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Anuruddha had gone into retreat for the day’s meditation. "

msgctxt "an8.46:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā manāpakāyikā devatā yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā devatā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then several deities of the Lovable Host went up to Venerable Anuruddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:1.4"
msgid "“mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, manāpakāyikā nāma devatā tīsu ṭhānesu issariyaṃ kārema vasaṃ vattema. "
msgstr "“Sir, Anuruddha, we are the deities called ‘Loveable’. We wield authority and control over three things. "

msgctxt "an8.46:1.5"
msgid "Mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, yādisakaṃ vaṇṇaṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ vaṇṇaṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma; "
msgstr "We can turn any color we want. "

msgctxt "an8.46:1.6"
msgid "yādisakaṃ saraṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ saraṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma; "
msgstr "We can get any voice that we want. "

msgctxt "an8.46:1.7"
msgid "yādisakaṃ sukhaṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ sukhaṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma. "
msgstr "We can get any pleasure that we want. "

msgctxt "an8.46:1.8"
msgid "Mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, manāpakāyikā nāma devatā imesu tīsu ṭhānesu issariyaṃ kārema vasaṃ vattemā”ti. "
msgstr "We are the deities called ‘Loveable’. We wield authority and control over these three things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.46:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato anuruddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Anuruddha thought, "

msgctxt "an8.46:2.2"
msgid "“aho vatimā devatā sabbāva nīlā assu nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā”ti. "
msgstr "“If only these deities would all turn blue, of blue color, clad in blue, adorned with blue!” "

msgctxt "an8.46:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā āyasmato anuruddhassa cittamaññāya sabbāva nīlā ahesuṃ nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā. "
msgstr "Then those deities, knowing Anuruddha’s thought, all turned blue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.46:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato anuruddhassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Anuruddha thought, "

msgctxt "an8.46:3.2"
msgid "“aho vatimā devatā sabbāva pītā assu … pe … "
msgstr "“If only these deities would all turn yellow …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:3.3"
msgid "sabbāva lohitakā assu … "
msgstr "“If only these gods would all turn red …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:3.4"
msgid "sabbāva odātā assu odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā”ti. "
msgstr "“If only these gods would all turn white …” "

msgctxt "an8.46:3.5"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā āyasmato anuruddhassa cittamaññāya sabbāva odātā ahesuṃ odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā. "
msgstr "Then those deities, knowing Anuruddha’s thought, all turned white. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.264, sc4
#. VAR: ca → ekāva (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: ca → ekāva (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: nacci ekā ca → ekāva (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.46:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā ekā ca gāyi ekā ca nacci ekā ca accharaṃ vādesi. "
msgstr "Then one of those deities sang, one danced, and one snapped her fingers. "

#. VAR: tūriyassa → turiyassa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.46:4.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma pañcaṅgikassa tūriyassa suvinītassa suppaṭipatāḷitassa kusalehi susamannāhatassa saddo hoti vaggu ca rajanīyo ca kamanīyo ca pemanīyo ca madanīyo ca; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a quintet made up of skilled musicians who had practiced well and kept excellent rhythm. They’d sound graceful, tantalizing, sensuous, lovely, and intoxicating. "

msgctxt "an8.46:4.3"
msgid "evamevaṃ tāsaṃ devatānaṃ alaṅkārānaṃ saddo hoti vaggu ca rajanīyo ca kamanīyo ca pemanīyo ca madanīyo ca. "
msgstr "In the same way the performance by those deities sounded graceful, tantalizing, sensuous, lovely, and intoxicating. "

msgctxt "an8.46:4.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho indriyāni okkhipi. "
msgstr "But Venerable Anuruddha averted his senses. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: na khvayyo → na kho ayyo (bj)
#. VAR: sādiyatī”ti → sādīyatīti (bj) | sādayatīti (saddanīti dhātumālā)
msgctxt "an8.46:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā “na khvayyo anuruddho sādiyatī”ti tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then those deities, thinking “Master Anuruddha isn’t enjoying this,” vanished right there. "

msgctxt "an8.46:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā anuruddho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Anuruddha came out of retreat and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened, adding: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an8.46:6.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, divāvihāraṃ gato homi paṭisallīno. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā manāpakāyikā devatā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, bhante, tā devatā maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.3"
msgid "‘mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, manāpakāyikā nāma devatā tīsu ṭhānesu issariyaṃ kārema vasaṃ vattema. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.4"
msgid "Mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, yādisakaṃ vaṇṇaṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ vaṇṇaṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.5"
msgid "yādisakaṃ saraṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ saraṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.6"
msgid "yādisakaṃ sukhaṃ ākaṅkhāma tādisakaṃ sukhaṃ ṭhānaso paṭilabhāma. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.7"
msgid "Mayaṃ, bhante anuruddha, manāpakāyikā nāma devatā imesu tīsu ṭhānesu issariyaṃ kārema vasaṃ vattemā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.8"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.9"
msgid "‘aho vatimā devatā sabbāva nīlā assu nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:6.10"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, tā devatā mama cittamaññāya sabbāva nīlā ahesuṃ nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.265, sc7
msgctxt "an8.46:7.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:7.2"
msgid "‘aho vatimā devatā sabbāva pītā assu … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:7.3"
msgid "sabbāva lohitakā assu … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:7.4"
msgid "sabbāva odātā assu odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:7.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, tā devatā mama cittamaññāya sabbāva odātā ahesuṃ odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an8.46:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, tā devatā ekā ca gāyi ekā ca nacci ekā ca accharaṃ vādesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:8.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma pañcaṅgikassa tūriyassa suvinītassa suppaṭipatāḷitassa kusalehi susamannāhatassa saddo hoti vaggu ca rajanīyo ca kamanīyo ca pemanīyo ca madanīyo ca; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:8.3"
msgid "evamevaṃ tāsaṃ devatānaṃ alaṅkārānaṃ saddo hoti vaggu ca rajanīyo ca kamanīyo ca pemanīyo ca madanīyo ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:8.4"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, bhante, indriyāni okkhipi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an8.46:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, tā devatā ‘na khvayyo anuruddho sādiyatī’ti tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.46:9.2"
msgid "Katihi nu kho, bhante, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti? "
msgstr "“How many qualities do females have so that—when their body breaks up, after death—they are reborn in company with the Gods of the Lovable Host?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an8.46:10.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhahi kho, anuruddha, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "“Anuruddha, when they have eight qualities females—when their body breaks up, after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Lovable Host. "

msgctxt "an8.46:10.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.46:10.3"
msgid "Idha, anuruddha, mātugāmo yassa mātāpitaro bhattuno denti atthakāmā hitesino anukampakā anukampaṃ upādāya tassa hoti pubbuṭṭhāyinī pacchānipātinī kiṅkārapaṭissāvinī manāpacārinī piyavādinī. (1) "
msgstr "Take the case of a female whose mother and father give her to a husband wanting what’s best for her, out of kindness and compassion. She would get up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: garuno → guruno (mr)
msgctxt "an8.46:11.1"
msgid "Ye te bhattu garuno honti—"
msgstr "She honors, respects, esteems, and venerates those her husband respects, such as "

msgctxt "an8.46:11.2"
msgid "mātāti vā pitāti vā samaṇabrāhmaṇāti vā—"
msgstr "mother and father, and ascetics and brahmins. "

#. VAR: garuṃ karoti → garukaroti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.46:11.3"
msgid "te sakkaroti, garuṃ karoti, māneti, pūjeti, abbhāgate ca āsanodakena paṭipūjeti. (2) "
msgstr "And when they arrive she serves them with a seat and water. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
#. VAR: tatrupāyāya → tatrūpāyāya (bj)
msgctxt "an8.46:12.1"
msgid "Ye te bhattu abbhantarā kammantā—uṇṇāti vā kappāsāti vā—tattha dakkhā hoti analasā tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgatā alaṃ kātuṃ alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ. (3) "
msgstr "She’s skilled and tireless in her husband’s household duties, such as knitting and sewing. She understands how to go about things in order to complete and organize the work. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.266, sc13
msgctxt "an8.46:13.1"
msgid "Yo so bhattu abbhantaro antojano—dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā—"
msgstr "She knows what work her husband’s domestic bondservants, employees, and workers have completed, and what they’ve left incomplete. "

#. VAR: paccaṃsena → paccayena (s1, s2) | paccayaṃsena (s3) | paccattaṃsena (mr)
msgctxt "an8.46:13.2"
msgid "tesaṃ katañca katato jānāti akatañca akatato jānāti, gilānakānañca balābalaṃ jānāti khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyañcassa paccaṃsena saṃvibhajati. (4) "
msgstr "She knows who is sick, and who is fit or unwell. She distributes to each a fair portion of various foods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an8.46:14.1"
msgid "Yaṃ bhattu āharati dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā taṃ ārakkhena guttiyā sampādeti, tattha ca hoti adhuttī athenī asoṇḍī avināsikā. (5) "
msgstr "She ensures that any income her husband earns is guarded and protected, whether money, grain, silver, or gold. She doesn’t overspend, steal, waste, or lose it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an8.46:15.1"
msgid "Upāsikā kho pana hoti buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā. (6) "
msgstr "She’s a lay follower who has gone for refuge to the Buddha, his teaching, and the Saṅgha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an8.46:16.1"
msgid "Sīlavatī kho pana hoti—"
msgstr "She’s ethical. "

msgctxt "an8.46:16.2"
msgid "pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā, adinnādānā paṭiviratā, kāmesumicchācārā paṭiviratā, musāvādā paṭiviratā, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā. (7) "
msgstr "She doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an8.46:17.1"
msgid "Cāgavatī kho pana hoti. "
msgstr "She’s generous. "

#. VAR: muttacāgā → muttacāgī (s1-3)
#. VAR: payatapāṇinī → payatapāṇi (bj) | payatapāṇī (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an8.46:17.2"
msgid "Vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgā payatapāṇinī vossaggaratā yācayogā dānasaṃvibhāgaratā. (8) "
msgstr "She lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an8.46:18.1"
msgid "Imehi kho, anuruddha, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatīti. "
msgstr "When they have these eight qualities females—when their body breaks up, after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Lovable Host. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an8.46:19.1"
msgid "Yo naṃ bharati sabbadā, "
msgstr "She’d never look down on her husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:19.2"
msgid "niccaṃ ātāpi ussuko; "
msgstr "who’s always keen to work hard, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:19.3"
msgid "Taṃ sabbakāmadaṃ posaṃ, "
msgstr "always looking after her, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:19.4"
msgid "bhattāraṃ nātimaññati. "
msgstr "and bringing whatever she wants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an8.46:20.1"
msgid "Na cāpi sotthi bhattāraṃ, "
msgstr "And a good woman never scolds her husband "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:20.2"
msgid "issāvādena rosaye; "
msgstr "with jealous words. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:20.3"
msgid "Bhattu ca garuno sabbe, "
msgstr "Being astute, she reveres "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:20.4"
msgid "paṭipūjeti paṇḍitā. "
msgstr "those respected by her husband. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
#. VAR: Uṭṭhāhikā → uṭṭhāyikā (mr)
msgctxt "an8.46:21.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhāhikā analasā, "
msgstr "She gets up early, works tirelessly, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:21.2"
msgid "saṅgahitaparijjanā; "
msgstr "and manages the domestic help. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:21.3"
msgid "Bhattu manāpaṃ carati, "
msgstr "She’s loveable to her husband, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:21.4"
msgid "sambhataṃ anurakkhati. "
msgstr "and preserves his wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "an8.46:22.1"
msgid "Yā evaṃ vattati nārī, "
msgstr "A lady who fulfills these duties "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:22.2"
msgid "bhattu chandavasānugā; "
msgstr "according to her husband’s desire, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Manāpā nāma te → manāpakāyikā (si, mr)
msgctxt "an8.46:22.3"
msgid "Manāpā nāma te devā, "
msgstr "is reborn among the gods "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an8.46:22.4"
msgid "yattha sā upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "called ‘Loveable’.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.46:22.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

